==English==

===Etymology===
From French [[automatique]], from {{Gr.}} '''[[αυτοματικός]]''' (''automatikos''), from  [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[αυτόματον]]''' (''automaton''), neutral of '''[[αυτόματος]]''' (''automatos'') "selfmoving, moving of oneself, self-acting, spontaneous",  from '''[[αυτός]]''' (''autos'') "self, myself" + '''[[μέμαα]]''' (''memaa'') "to wish eagerly, strive, yearn, desire".

===Adjective===
'''automatic'''

# Capable of operating without external control or intervention.
#: ''The automatic clothes washer was a great labor-saving device''
# Acting out of habit; without conscious thought.
#: ''My reaction of fear was automatic.''
#Describes a firearm which fires continuously as long as the trigger is pressed and [[ammunition]] is not exhausted. Used regarding [[machine pistol]]s, [[submachine gun]]s, or [[machine gun]]s.

===Noun===
'''automatic'''

# A [[car]] with automatic [[transmission]].
#: ''I never learned to drive a stick.  I can only drive an automatic.''
#A [[semi-automatic]] [[pistol]] is often referred to as an automatic, although this is not strictly correct.

